{
	"description": "Retained-submodule contract (restructure plan Phase 5; docs/architecture/repository-structure.md §Retained Submodule Contract). Records, per .gitmodules entry, what every retained submodule must provide: owners, engine metadata, peer ranges, required commands, and versioning policy. Validated by scripts/check-submodule-contracts.mjs in CI (clean-clone + package gates). Owners stay explicitly 'unknown' until CODEOWNERS or equivalent evidence exists (plan §4/§27).",
	"gitlinkProcess": "Gitlink bumps land as dedicated superproject commits after the submodule commit is pushed to its remote; path moves use a dedicated PR that updates .gitmodules and gitlinks atomically and passes the clean-clone workflow (plan §18).",
